166 J YRANSLA TJONS.

V10. A blank, my lord. She never told her love, But let concealment, like a worm i’ the bud, Feed on her damask cheek: she pined in thought, And with a green and yellow melancholy She sat like patience on a monument, Smiling at grief. Was not this love indeed? We men may say more, swear moref but indeed Our shows are more than will; for still we prove Much in our vows, but little in our love.

‚SHAKESPEARIL
